    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Wilhelmine refers to the period of German history beginning with the proclamation of Wilhelm I as Kaiser in 1871 and ending with the abdication of Wilhelm II in 1918. Wilhelmine (or 'Wilhelminist') style is marked by imperial grandiosity expressed in a neo-Baroque vocabulary of forms.</Note_Text>
